We can easily simplify this equation: \begin{align*}
x^2+y^2 + 3 &= -4y + 6x-1\\
x^2+y^2 +4&= 6x -4y \\
x^2-6x + y^2 + 4&=0\\
\end{align*}Which leaves us with a circle:
\begin{align*}
(x-3)^2+(y-0)^2 &= 1^2\\
(x-3)^2+y^2&=1\\
\end{align*}
Therefore, the area of the region bounded by this equation is simply $\pi$.
